:section[align:center](#why-slamhaus)

## 💡 Why Slamhaus?

:column[size:3](#slamhaus-pillars)

### 🧠  
### Built Like a Game Engine

Slamhaus uses a modular C++17 architecture — no global state, no magic. Each system (parsing, rendering, templating, SEO) is designed like a game engine subsystem: isolated, predictable, and ready for extension.

:column[2]()

### 🧬  
### No JavaScript? No Problem.

With built-in WebAssembly support via [Emscripten](https://emscripten.org/), Slamhaus lets you write dynamic frontend logic in C++. Bind UI elements to native functions with `@script[]()` — no JavaScript required.

:column[3]()

### ✍️  
### Markdown That Works Like Code

Slamhaus extends Markdown with readable, composable tags: `:section[]()` for layout, `?form[]()` for interactivity, `$page[]()` for metadata. It’s Markdown — but smarter, cleaner, and compiler-friendly.

:/column

:/section

