:section[align:center](#core-highlights)

## 🎨 Core Features at a Glance

:column[size:3](#core-row-1)


### 📝  
### Markdown → HTML

Write `.slam`, `.smd`, or `.md` files — Slamhaus generates fully static, styled HTML output with zero client-side runtime.

:column[2]()

### ⚙️  
### C++17 Engine

Built in modern C++ for speed and modularity. Familiar to devs from game, systems, or embedded backgrounds.

:column[3]()

### 🧩  
### Extended Syntax

Layout, forms, metadata, and scripting — all handled with clean, expressive Markdown tags like `:section[]()` and `?button[]()`.

:/column

<br>

:column[size:3](#core-row-2)


### 🧠  
### WebAssembly Support

Write C++ functions and bind them to UI elements using `@script[]()`. Slamhaus compiles and wires up everything — no JS glue required.

:column[2]()

### 🎨  
### Tweakable Themes

Minimal CSS by default. Drop your own styles into `content/assets/theme/` to customize or replace. All styles are inlined for performance.

:column[3]()

### 🔗  
### Smart Link Rewriting

Use `.slam`, `.smd`, or `.md` in your links — Slamhaus rewrites them to `.html` automatically, even inside metadata and buttons.

:/column

:/section

